<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PaLTM3.5.11">
<l>aravil paḷḷikoṇ ṭaravam turantiṭ</l>
<l rend="indent">ṭaravap pakaiyūr tiyava ṉuṭaiya</l>
<l>kuraviṟ koṭimul laikaḷniṉ ṟuṟaṅkuṅ</l>
<l rend="indent">kōvart taṉameṉ ṉuṅkoṟṟak kuṭaimēl</l>
<l>tiruviṟ poli maṟaivā ṇarputtūrt</l>
<l rend="indent">tikaḻpaṭ ṭarpirāṉ coṉṉamā laipattum</l>
<l>paravu maṉanaṉ kuṭaippat taruḷḷār</l>
<l rend="indent">paramā ṉavaikun tamnaṇṇu varē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Devotees who have goodness in [their] minds</l>
<l>that praise [this] garland of ten [verses],</l>
<l>composed by the lord [and] shining scholar of Puttūr,</l>
<l rend="indent">[where] Brahmins flourish in holiness,</l>
<l>on the victory umbrella called Govardhana,</l>
<l rend="indent">where jasmine creepers stay, slumbering on bottle flowers,</l>
<l>of him who rides the enemy of snakes,</l>
<l rend="indent">[who] has a serpent bed, [who] drove off the serpent,</l>
<l>[they] will reach supreme Vaikuntha!</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
